==================

1. TWO SUM II (Sorted Array)
   Problem: Find two numbers that add up to target
   Approach:
       left = 0, right = n-1
       while left < right:
           sum = arr[left] + arr[right]
           if sum == target:
               return [left, right]
           elif sum < target:
               left++
           else:
               right--

2. VALID PALINDROME
   Problem: Check if string is palindrome (ignoring spaces/special chars)
   Approach:
       left = 0, right = n-1
       while left < right:
           skip non-alphanumeric from left
           skip non-alphanumeric from right
           if char[left] != char[right]:
               return false
           left++
           right--
       return true

3. REVERSE STRING
   Problem: Reverse a string in-place
   Approach:
       left = 0, right = n-1
       while left < right:
           swap(arr[left], arr[right])
           left++
           right--

